user_score_effect = []
for plat in data_recent['platform'].unique():
    x = data_recent[(data['platform'] == plat)]['user_score']
    y = data_recent[(data['platform'] == plat)]['world_sales']
    correlation = y.corr(x)
    user_score_effect.append(correlation)
    print(f'       {plat}   ', correlation)
    print('   ', len(x))
    print('   ', len(x.unique()))

data1 = data_recent.loc[data['platform'] == 'XOne']['user_score'].dropna()

alpha = 0.05

t_stat, p_value = stats.ttest_ind(data1, data2, equal_var=False)

if p_value < alpha:
    print(f"  ")
else:
    print("    ")
